{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4b7430e6-3223-400e-9d9a-7869a12a6461","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"99e13430-eb01-4855-84e8-9ea72eb6fdbb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":352,"requestId":"8430:252037:1DF991C:214B1D5:6A0ACE7D"},"id":"aaee2c62-3933-45f8-9c91-cf19ada25148","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:32:04.450Z","parentId":"c4421bac-3e44-4cae-9f05-f13ae6315bd6"}
